post_text:
We will never forget! As we honor Patriot's Day, Mrs. Savas's class took time to honor our Patriot Day Heroes by remembering their courage and bravery. As a class, they read letters written to the 9/11 heroes from children in 2001. They discussed how much we all appreciate our heroes. Mrs. Savas's class also wrote their own thank you letters to our 9/11 heroes and completed acrostic poems in hearts colored in red, white, and blue! What a beautiful way to remember this day.

One special quote that may help some to get through this emotional day was once shared by Mr. Fred Rogers, "When I was a boy and I would see scary things in the news,‚Äù Rogers said to his television neighbors, ‚Äúmy mother would say to me, 'Look for the helpers. You will always find people who are helping. ' #swsdproud #wewillneverforget #lookforthehelpers

Beginning on Wednesday, September 9th, the Swedesboro-Woolwich School District Lunch Program will be free to all enrolled students and their siblings under the age of 18. This means that students who normally pay for school lunch may now receive free lunch. Based on the current guidance from the USDA, this will remain in effect until December 31, 2020.

You can find more information on the District main website by clicking on the fork and knife icon. You can also find more information on our District Reopening Site (Click on Lunch Time).

The order form can be found here: https://forms.gle/mmfXJgKpsG4Lj6WY8

post_text:
This year SWSD will host our first Virtual Open House on Thursday, September 3 (4:30 pm - 6:30 pm). We have decided to go virtual for 2 reasons:

a) No gatherings larger than 25 are permitted in one space at this time (i.e. a classroom)

b) As outlined in the District's Reopening Plan, the District is limiting visitors, outside groups, and guests inside our school buildings until we open for full-capacity instruction.

Although SWSD acknowledges "COVID-19 policies are intended to mitigate, not eliminate, risk, and no single action or set of actions will completely eliminate the risk of SARS-CoV-2 transmission.... implementation of several coordinated interventions can greatly reduce that risk.‚Äù As such, SWSD is adhering to social distancing guidelines and recommendations when possible to the best of our ability. (American Academy of Pediatrics)

Summer information was sent to the post office today, and more information about the Virtual Open House will be provided to you by your child's classroom teacher. Be sure to review your school messenger account to confirm you are receiving emails in the manner you prefer. Most District emails are sent as "general" email.

During our Virtual Open House - students will be able to virtually see their classrooms and their 2020 - 2021 school year teacher! #swsdproud #swsdreopening2020

post_text: Parent reminder: This school year promises to be one for the history books! We are beginning a school year in two brand new models (Hybrid which meets social distancing guidelines & Distance Learning - 100% remote). However if we need to address student or staff health concerns, plans can change over night. Every decision will be situation dependent. So please be sure to have a back- up plan if your child is required to isolate or quarantine. Prepare in advance if your child‚Äôs classroom is required to close. These decisions will be made whenever necessary and due to the circumstances - without warning. #backupplan #bestpreparedplans #timetoplan

post_text:
Dear SWSD Families,

Due to the very recent statement shared today by Governor Murphy and in anticipation of updated guidelines for reopening our schools, the Swedesboro-Woolwich Board of Education will be canceling this evening's Board of Education Meeting in order to provide the District with the critical and much needed time to review and analyze today's very recent information. I, along with hundreds of Superintendents and Boards of Education across our state, are in need of time to review these updates as the reopening of our schools is a major undertaking.

The District already has a meeting scheduled on August 26, 2020. If the District is in need of scheduling a special meeting next week, this meeting will be announced to the community as soon as possible.

post_text:
Beginning this weekend, SWSD will begin sharing out quick updates and tid-bits for our families. It's our "Reopening PSAs." Small pieces of information and reminders for families may be helpful.

Today's question: What will a school classroom look like?

Here is a sample of classroom set-up at the Harker School. (Please keep in mind that staff are not permitted to return yet to begin their organizing process.)

Our very large and complete district plan will be posted once the plan receives the required approval of compliance by the NJDOE. It will be emailed out and posted on our District Reopening Website.

Be sure to check the Reopening website once a week to review updates. We are continually adding to our FAQs. If you take time to review it for updates once a week, that is PERFECT! )

Throughout the month brief updates, videos, and reminders will be shared.

post_text: The Statewide Equity in Action Unconference was held this week. There were so many amazing sessions from which to choose. Dr. O'Neil and Mrs. Teague participated in one or more of the following sessions: Social Emotional Toolbox, A Strategy for Predominately White School Districts & the Achievement/Opportunity Gap, Classroom Strategies to Promote Acceleration and Equity for Struggling Students, and Say It Loud! (the importance of being actively anti-racist in our educational practice at the elementary level). Although we missed being there in person, this was an awesome way to gather 2,000 educators across the state. #swsdproud #swsdsummerlearning

Board of Education Vacancy

The Swedesboro-Woolwich Board of Education is seeking interested applicants to fill a vacancy on the Board of Education. Applicants may submit a cover letter/statement of interest and resume to the attention of Chris DeStratis-Board Secretary, on or before 4:00 pm Monday, July 13, 2020. Confirmed applicants will receive an invitation to speak on their behalf during the Board‚Äôs regular meeting at 6:30 pm on Wednesday, July 29, 2020. The Board will appoint their selected applicant before adjourning the meeting on July 29, 2020.

Mr. Christopher J. DeStratis
School Business Administrator/Board Secretary
Swedesboro-Woolwich Board of Education
15 Fredrick Blvd

Attention ALL PK - Gr. 5 SWSD Families: SWSD is asking for your time and participation in our 2020 - 2021 SWSD Re-Opening Survey. The creation of the survey includes questions suggested and reviewed by members of the 2020 SWSD Re-Opening District Committee. The District Committee is made up of 27 staff members (Administrators, Certificated Staff, and Non-Certificated Staff).

This survey is comprised of 30 questions. We ask that you answer every question in the survey. It will take approximately 15 - 20 minutes of your time to complete. You may wish to complete this survey together WITH your child/children by asking for his/her/their input, too. If you do not wish to answer an open-ended question, please type a "0" or N/A in the box.

Although you will only be permitted to complete this survey once, you will be permitted to edit your responses through 6/30/2020 by accessing the available link.

https://www.surveymonkey.com/r/RC3CGFX

Good morning. We hope everyone is doing well! We just wanted to give you a quick update on the 2019-20 Swedesboro/Woolwich Yearbook. Since the printing plant was shut down for a while, the yearbooks are just now being printed. We expect to have a July delivery. Once we receive the yearbooks, we will notify you regarding the pickup dates/times/procedures.

We will be taking orders for the yearbook until we receive the delivery. Now is the time to get your last minute order in for the book. Mrs. Hubbard has put extraordinary effort into the book and it is going to be a special "quarantine" edition. The link to order online from Balfour is: https://www.balfour.com/student-info?smi=134311 and can also be found on the Swedesboro-Woolwich School District website under "Announcements."

If you have any questions, please feel free to reply to this email or email Deb at dstatile@swsdk6.com.

post_text:
School closures can't keep us away from our math! This past February, the Harker School Math League Team took 1st place in a math qualifying competition held at the Mastery Charter Thomas Elementary School in PA. This earned them a spot to compete at the New Jersey State Level Mathleague.Org Competition.

Congratulations to the Harker School Math League Team who placed 8 out of 17 overall at the state level. Extra special congratulations to Ryan Duffy (grade 5) who placed 14 out of 40 and Olivia Adamek (grade 4) who placed 17 out of 37. We have some stellar mathematicians among us! It may have been hard work, but our students made sure to take time to pose for the CHS paparazzi.

Way to go Math League Team!!! #swsdproud

Dear SWSD Families,

We are sincerely asking for your feedback. This is our second District Parent Survey distributed to the entire district, and your input is important to us. You may notice that many of the questions are the same as those that appeared in the first parent survey distributed on April 3, 2020. This is intentional in that it will help us to monitor perception over time. Please take a few minutes to help guide our District in providing the best virtual learning experience that we can for your child. We still have many weeks of new learning ahead of us and your input is critically important to us. Please complete the survey by Saturday, May 16, 2020.

Our SWSD Community Heroes never take a break! #swsdproud

Good Morning,

The Swedesboro-Woolwich school district, partnering with the HEADstrong Foundation, is excited to announce our first ever Virtual 1 mile Fun Run/Walk to support cancer patients and their families!

Registration for this virtual event will begin on Monday, May 4th and will remain open until Sunday, May 17. By pledging $5, you can complete the run/walk anywhere you want, any day you want, just before Sunday, May 17th.

As your family runs/walks, snap pictures and post on social media with #SWSDProud. We will feature them on our District's social media pages!

Our country may be in a lockdown, but cancer never stops. Register today at:

https://pledge.headstrong.org/event/be-a-hero-fun-run-walk/e278170

Stay tuned for a chance to WIN during an HEADstrong Scavenger Hunt. More details will be announced on Wednesday, but you can prepare by decorating the HEADstrong sneaker!

(https://drive.google.com/file/d/1R1N02ZNh8xDQIrNLaql5R9EX__RwA6Ew/view)

ATTENTION FAMILIES WHO RECEIVE FREE OR REDUCED LUNCH IN SWSD:

During this school closure period, a local business has offered to provide assistance to our families who receive free or reduced lunch while SWSD is closed.

However, the school is not permitted to release protected information. If you are in need of assistance and willing to share your information with the local business and Woolwich Twp., please contact me as soon as you are able: koneil@swsdk6.com or (856) 241-1552 (ext. 1006).

We are all here to assist one another during this challenging time.

However, the school is not permitted to release protected information. If you are in need of assistance and willing to share your information with the local business and Woolwich Twp., please contact me as soon as you are able: koneil@swsdk6.com or (856) 241-1552 (ext. 1006).

We are all here to assist one another during this challenging time.

post_text: Thank You Philly Pretzel Factory in Logan Township!
shared_text:
Philly Pretzel Factory - Logan Township
March 15 at 4:49 PM ¬∑

"EVERY KID EATS"
Starting tomorrow Philly Pretzel Factory will implement a program where every Child/Student receives 2 FREE PRETZELS until classes are back in session!

With school out for a few weeks and everyone out there trying to adjust their schedules. Staying healthy & maintaining some sort of routine is essential. We're happy to offer our assistance to any student needing a meal!

Stop in anytime between 10am - 2pm Monday thru Friday for 2 FREE PRETZELS. This applies to any child/student and will run until school are up and running again! If there are any special circumstances out there that you feel that we could help with, PLEASE add them to the Comment Section!

We urge all restaurants to take part. Together We Make The Difference in our Community!üòä

post_text:
The SWSD ABA Preschool program will be going on TWO field trips to We Rock the Spectrum this Winter thanks to our community sponsors, Okinawa Kenpo Karate Academy & Heritage's!

We Rock the Spectrum (WRTS) is a gym that is committed to providing a safe, nurturing, and fun environment to foster learning, exploration and appropriate sensory experiences for children across the autistic spectrum.

The gym is PERFECT for our students with their various sensory items for them to play with and on, quiet places to decompress and great activities to work on their gross and fine motor skills.

Because of their generous sponsorship, during each field trip to WTRS, the preschool ABA students will have endless social and physical opportunities with hands-on equipment assisting in their neurological growth and development!

THANK YOU Okinawa Kenpo Karate Academy & Heritage's! #swsdproud

@GloucesterCountyKarate @heritagedairy @WRTSaudubon

post_text:
Attention Hill School Students! Are you interested?

https://forms.gle/pFdZHNqno48GsSS88

WHS is looking for a student Green Team! The Green Team will act as student ambassadors to help reduce plastic use in our school, and will meet as a cohort for the rest of the year (similar to student council). An announcement will be made tomorrow morning introducing the Green Team.

Thanks for your help!

post_text:
Thank you West Deptford Township Schools and West Deptford High School students & administration. You truly made a difference in the lives of children and families beyond your own immediate community.

This year West Deptford was fortunate that their Operation Blessing collection was so successful that they were able to donate to the families and students of SWSD. THANK YOU WDHS PRINCIPAL, DR. GISMONDI, & WDHS for reaching out to us, and thank you for modeling how when we all work together we build a better world. @WDHigh

West Deptford School District #westdeptfordhs #swsdproud
